       <p class="meta"><span itemprop="creator" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><a href="/" rel="author" itemprop="name">Mathias</a></span> wrote on <time datetime="2012-01-31T23:03" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="#comment-15" rel="bookmark" itemprop="url" title="Permanent link to comment 15 on “How to create simple Mac apps from shell scripts”">31st January 2012 at 23:03</a></time>:</p>
      </header>
      <div itemprop="commentText">
       <p>Thomas created an updated version of Appify that adds OS X 10.7 Lion support by also creating an <code>Info.plist</code> file: <a href="https://github.com/subtleGradient/tilde-bin/blob/master/appify">https://github.com/subtleGradient/tilde-bin/blob/master/appify</a></p>
       <p>There’s a UI for Appify, too: <a href="https://github.com/subtleGradient/Appify-UI">https://github.com/subtleGradient/Appify-UI</a></p>
      </div>
     </article>
