     <article id="comment-26" data-id="909" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments">
      <header>
       <div class="avatar"><img src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/bde1b58dbfb3dd9610d94f10821ae87b?s=30" alt="" width="30" height="30" srcset="https://gravatar.com/avatar/bde1b58dbfb3dd9610d94f10821ae87b?s=60 2x"></div>
       <p class="meta"><span itemprop="creator" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name">Gino</span></span> wrote on <time datetime="2013-10-18T13:59" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="#comment-26" rel="bookmark" itemprop="url" title="Permanent link to comment 26 on “How to create simple Mac apps from shell scripts”">18th October 2013 at 13:59</a></time>:</p>
      </header>
      <div itemprop="commentText">
       <p>This “appify” is quite useless… It’s far easier (and gives fewer problems with scripts) to follow this procedure:</p>
       <ol>
        <li>Create your shell script (ex <code>command.sh</code>)</li>
        <li>Give it execution permissions (<code>chmod 755 ./command.sh</code>)</li>
        <li>Get Info → Open with: → (associate the Terminal app)</li>
        <li>Get Info → (put the icon you want on it)</li>
       </ol>
       <p>Kind Regards,<br>
       Gino</p>
      </div>
     </article>
